    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Specifying your app’s color scheme"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "accent color",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ", or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "tint color",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ", is a broad theme color that applies to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "views and controls in your app.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Use an accent color to quickly create a unifying color scheme for your app.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "You can set an accent for your app by specifying an accent color in your asset catalog.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "specifying-your-apps-color-scheme-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-an-accent-color-set",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create an accent color set",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you create your project from a template, it automatically includes a default asset",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "catalog (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Assets.xcassets",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ") with an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AccentColor",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " color set. Xcode applies the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "color you specify in this color set as your app’s accent color.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If your app doesn’t have an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AccentColor",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " color set, create a color set manually.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In the Project navigator, select an asset catalog.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Click the Add button (+) at the bottom of the outline view.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In the pop-up menu, choose Color Set. A new color set appears in the outline",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "view, and opens in the detail area.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Double-click the color set name in the outline view to rename the color set",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "with a descriptive name, and press the Return key.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In Build Settings, find the build setting for “Global Accent Color Name”.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Double-click the build setting, type in the name of your accent color set,",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "and press Return.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Specify-accent-color-variations",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Specify accent color variations",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you select an accent color, choose a color that works well in light and dark",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "appearances. In your accent color set, you can specify different color values for",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "light and dark appearances if necessary.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In the Project navigator, select an asset catalog.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In the outline view, select the accent color set.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Open the Attributes inspector. In the Appearances field, choose the appearances",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "for which you want to specify color values. Additional wells appear in the detail area",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "for the appearance options you specify.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Select a well, and set a color by using the Content field in the Attributes inspector.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Use the Any Appearance well to specify the color value the app uses on systems that",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "don’t differentiate between light and dark appearances.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can also specify high-contrast versions of your colors by selecting the High Contrast checkbox.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Access-the-accent-color-from-your-code",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Access the accent color from your code",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "By default, your accent color applies to all views and controls in your app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that use a tint color, unless you override the color for a specific subset of the view hierarchy.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "However, you might want to incorporate the accent color into other parts of your user interface",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that don’t rely on a tint color, like static text elements.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To use the accent color value from an asset catalog in code, load the color like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "// SwiftUI",
            "Text(\"Accent Color\")",
            "    .foregroundStyle(Color.accentColor)",
            "",
            "// UIKit",
            "label.textColor = UIColor.tintColor"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
